description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Advert - Director of Business Intelligence&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;West Hertfordshire Hospitals NHS Trust is seeking to appoint a dynamic and accomplished professional Director of Business Intelligence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity for an experienced analytics professional to drive and lead a Business Intelligence team to support West Hertfordshire Hospitals NHS Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will develop a team tasked with implementing and optimising tools and strategies to translate raw data into valuable insights that guide the Trust. You will develop and optimise core analytics visualisation tools, delivering insights that empower the Trust and Senior Management team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will also play an important role in the evolution of our organisation, be it our Integrated Care Partnership, our EPR programme or the building of our new hospital&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As you will play a meaningful role in the team, we expect you to have strong logical reasoning skills, strong insight and analytics development skills, and be experienced in optimising data visualisation. You will drive requirement gathering and analytics developments with an aim towards putting data &amp; technology at the heart of everything we do in the organisation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;West Hertfordshire Hospital Trust is an organisation on the move, if you wish to be a big part of our exciting future then please apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note interview date 4th December 2020.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Pauline O&#39;Connor Job title Executive Assistant,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;email: Pauline.o’connor1@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
